# LLM-assisted development (essentials)

**Read order:** [AGENTS.md](../../AGENTS.md) ‚Üí this file (always on) ‚Üí [CLAUDE.md](../../CLAUDE.md) only for `upload`/Konflux/image ‚Üí [docs/ARCHITECTURE.md](../../docs/ARCHITECTURE.md) when touching multiple packages. **Extended detail** (per-tool lint commands, long PR template, troubleshooting): [.cursor/rules/llm-development-guidelines-deep.mdc](llm-development-guidelines-deep.mdc) ‚Äî use `@llm-development-guidelines-deep` in Cursor when needed.

## Domain

- **Pulp** API semantics: [pulpproject.org](https://pulpproject.org/)
- **Commands & conventions:** `AGENTS.md` ¬∑ **Konflux contracts:** `CLAUDE.md` ¬∑ **Code map:** `docs/ARCHITECTURE.md`

## Pull requests and CHANGELOG

- **Do not** paste a full PR body every turn. If the turn might become a PR, **ask once** if the user wants paste-ready PR text.
- **After they confirm:** provide PR text that **follows `.github/PULL_REQUEST_TEMPLATE.md` verbatim**: use the same **`##` headings** in order (`## Summary`, `## How to test`, `## Checklist`, `## Notes for reviewers`), keep the **checklist lines** as written (typically unchecked `- [ ]` items), then fill **Summary** / **How to test** / **Notes**‚Äîdo not substitute a different outline. Also provide a suggested commit (`Assisted-By:` + `Signed-off-by:` per `.github/commit-message-template.txt`), and **`CHANGELOG.md`** under `[Unreleased]` when notable ‚Äî **same turn**. Full detail: **deep** rule ¬ß *GitHub PR description*.
- **No** `CHANGELOG` edits on every debug fix unless the user asks.
- **Merge gate:** **100% diff coverage** on the PR diff (`make test-diff-coverage`). Overall project % is separate.

## After code changes (mandatory)

1. `make lint` ‚Üí fix issues
2. `make format`
3. `pre-commit run --all-files` ‚Üí **loop** until **zero** failures
4. `make test` (full suite) ‚Üí **loop** until green
5. `git fetch origin` ‚Üí `make test-diff-coverage` (use `COMPARE_BRANCH=origin/<base>` if not targeting `main`) ‚Üí **loop** until diff is fully covered

Do not treat the branch as PR-ready without clean pre-commit, green tests, and passing diff-cover.

